summary: So I told you I dived into WinterIron fics and just... GAAAHHHH OH MY GAWD. You know, there are powerful fics and then...
question: So I told you I dived into WinterIron fics and just... GAAAHHHH OH MY GAWD. You know, there are powerful fics and then there's... 60k of plot, fluffy ending, only for one line to reduce me INTO A FUCKING MESS KDJHAKD holy shit like... just... dear lord this shi was probably low key meant as a joke and low key a sequel door but Im just sitting here so fucking mad at this line. (the fic is great. called "Still alive" and has like 4 authors, but it's because of imbedded art)
answer:
I do not have the attentionspan for 60k+ words of fanfiction. ô___Ô

And it’s really good? Like really really good? And the way that line turned you into a mess is not negative? *pokes it with a stick*

blog.description:
Ask Box is always open! 🌻🌻 |MasterList

⚡️“ᴵ ᴬᴹ ᴹᴵᴳᴴᵀᵞ” ⚡️

I’m just a Teenager who likes to write.

body:
But My Cat •SpiderMan•

Warnings: Language!

You were currently on your way to Germany. As crazy as that seems, yes you were skipping school and that ruined your perfect attendance but you didn’t care at the moment. You were actually sitting behind the famous Clint Barton and Wanda Maximoff as you squeezed yourself next to the door as a man named Scott was taking up the seat.

“We’re almost there Y/N, thank you for agreeing to this.” Clint said as he pulled into a parking garage of what seemed to be an airport.

You shrugged. “I’m 16, got to live a little.” You said causing him to laugh slightly.

“Yeah, we need young people on the team.” He chuckled causing Wanda to roll her eyes.

“We have arrived.” Wanda said. Her accent thick and strong yet sounded bored.

Clint parked the van and opened the door so you could get out before he woke up Scott.

Walking around the car your breath caught in your throat as the Captain America stood in front of you.

It wouldn’t be a lie if you said he didn’t look confused on why a 16 year old girl was in front of him.

“Steve Rogers.” He said as he offered his hand out.

“Y-Y/N L/N.” You said as you did your best to give him a firm handshake.

“You go by Shadow Correct? And I assume that’s because of the dark magic?” Steve asked as his curiosity slipped through.

You nodded. “Yes sir. I’m able to control the dark arts you could say. I’m also kinda like those people who do the weird Voodoo doll stuff.” You said laughing slightly.

Steve nodded. “That sounds….interesting.” He said as he was slightly unsure.

About 20 minutes later when everyone was geared up you had a plan. Steve would walk out and gather Tony’s attention, Bucky and Sam would go through the Airport itself, and you, Clint, and Scott would be ready Incase something happened to Steve.

“Wow, it’s so weird how you run into people at the airport. Don’t you think?” Tony asked Rhodes as they were playing in the air with the IronMan and WarMachine suit.

“Definitely weird.” Rhodes replied.

Steve slowly walked foreword as he replied. “Hear me out, Tony. That doctor, the psychiatrist, he’s behind all of this.” Steve said as he walked out with cautious hands.

“Captain.” T'Challa said as he appeared next to Tony who landed with Rhodes.

“Your highness.” Steve replied plainly before Tony spoke.

“Anyway. Ross gave me 36 hours to bring you in. That was 24 hours ago. Can you help a brother out?” He asked as he truly didn’t want to fight his friend.

“You’re after the wrong guy.” Steve said softly, knowing where this would lead to.

“Your judgment is askew. Your war buddy killed innocent people yesterday.” Tony said as he started to get irritated.

Before Steve could reply, Natasha spoke as you peaked up slightly to see but Clint pulled you down. “Steve. You know what’s about to happen. Do you really wanna punch your way out of this one?” She asked.

‘Omg. That was such a cool one liner!’ You thought as you closed your eyes to listen better.

“Alright. I’ve run out of patience. Underoos!” Tony yelled before all of a sudden Steve’s hands were webbed together and his Shield was gone.

“What the hell.” You muttered. “Clint we have to do something.” You said turning towards him.

“Not yet Y/N.” He whispered.

“Good job kid.” Tony said before the kid spoke and something jolted in your mind.

“Thanks. Well, I could’ve stuck the landing a little better. It’s….just the new suit…..Well, it’s nothing Mr. Stark, it’s-it’s perfect.” The Spider-Boy said.

But something about that seemed familiar. The way he said “Mr. Stark.” Jogged your memory but you couldn’t place it.

You didn’t really pick up some of their next conversation since you were busy thinking but Tony yelling got your attention.

“And you’ve been a complete idiot! Dragging in Clint. Rescuing Wanda from a place she doesn’t even want to leave. A safe place. I’m trying to keep…. I’m trying to keep you from tearing the Avengers apart.” Tony said, clearly irritated.

“You did that when you signed.” Steve said as you secretly wished he had kept his mouth shut.

“Alright. I’m done. You’re gonna turn Barnes over and you’re going to come with us. Now! Because it’s us! We’re squaded JSOC, guys, with no compunction about being impolite.” Tony said.

All of a sudden before anyone could speak, Sam’s voice was heard in your ear. “We found it. The quinjets in hanger 5, north runway.” He said before Clint turned to you.

“Ready Y/N? Just like we talked about.” He said before you nodded.

Clint quickly stood up from your hiding spot shooting an arrow through Steve’s locked hands as he put his arms up while you used your magic to push Team IronMan back further.

“What….what the hell was that?” Rhodes asked after you pushed them and as Scott kicked SpiderBoy in the jaw.

“I believe this is your Captain America.” He said handing over Steves Shield.

The next thing you knew you were running down the airport runway slightly ahead of Clint as it was you and him just doing plain cardio.

You saw the SpiderBoy swing into the airport terminal to find Wilson and Barnes but you knew the two grown men could handle the kid as you raced to fight this robot named Vision, you had no clue who he was but he seemed pretty useless.

A couple minutes later the SpiderBoy has come back out of the terminal looking unharmed. “I got the SpiderKid.” You said into your com.

“Go for it Shadow.” Steve replied as he sounded out of breath and exhausted.

Running towards him you used your Voodoo magic to make him freeze before landing a punch right across his jaw.

“Ow! Hey-what the hell?!” He whined as your magic lifted sending him to the ground.

“Don’t go easy on his Y/N. He’s on the wrong side.” Sam said through your coms.

You then swirled your hands using your dark magic to lift him into the air and spread his lips stretching him to the point where he was yelling.

“Hey!! Hey hey! Okay! Stop! Please!” He shouted, but you held him still.

“Where did you get these powers?” He asked as he struggled slightly.

“Let’s just say I read the wrong book in the library.” You replied before you noticed he dropped to the floor landing in a small pose and your hands were webbed. “What?” You asked yourself.

“Called a distraction.” He said before swiftly jumping up and kicking you across the face; kicking the small mask you had off.

“Y-Y/N?!” He gasped as he watched you use your magic to break through his web fluid.

“I knew it was you.” You muttered as you watched him pull his mask off. “Peter.” You nodded.

“What-what are you doing here?” He stuttered.

“Clearly helping the Captain America. What about you? You’re suppose to be watching my cat!” You said slightly agitated.

“Uh. About that, I asked Ned to watch your cat Scarlett.” He said while rubbing the back of his neck.

“You asked NED!!” You screamed.

“Hey. Kid, what’s with all the talking and not fighting?!.” Tony asked Peter through the earpiece.

“Oh uh… sorry Mr. Stark, just have some complications. No worry though.” He rambled.

“You’re seriously on Tony’s side?” You asked.

“And you’re on Captain America’s? Mr. Stark asked for help and I couldn’t turn him down!” Peter explained. “You know how much I look up to Mr. Stark.” He said.

You frowned as you knew Peter was right. “I understand that Peter but I’m not fighting you.” You said backing away as you grabbed your mask. “We’ll talk later, but for now I have a job to do. So stay out of the way.” You said before giving him a small smile and rubbing off.

You frowned as you knew Peter was right. “I understand that Peter but I’m not fighting you.” You said backing away as you grabbed your mask. “We’ll talk later, but for now I have a job to do. So stay out of the way.” You said before giving him a small smile and rubbing off.
